Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.30,0:00:06.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Found within Uncle Kogorou's wallet\Nwas a receipt for a 50,000 yen necklace.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.80,0:00:13.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seemed to be birthday present for Ran's mother,\NAttorney Kisaki, who was born on October 10th.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.40,0:00:10.15,title01,,0,0,0,,{\be0.5\fad(0,370)}October 10th
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.27,0:00:11.02,title01,,0,0,0,,{\be0.5\fad(0,370)}October 10th
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.44,0:00:20.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After learning of that, Ran displayed he tremendous\Nlottery luck and won the hotel stay prize from it.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.78,0:00:28.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As a result, we ended up sitting at a fancy\Ndinner table in a sea-side hotel, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.75,0:00:33.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Uncle didn't seem to plan to give her the present,\Nand even fell asleep due to his drunkenness.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.17,0:00:37.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Attorney Kisaki became irritated and returned to her room.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.67,0:00:43.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just before midnight and the end of the birthday...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.43,0:00:46.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ran tried to get Uncle to deliver his present at any cost.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.64,0:00:52.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But soon after we barged into the room,\Nwe discovered a murdered female body.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.94,0:01:03.33,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,That woman was Kokubu Akiho{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, a client of Attorney Kisaki\Nwho requested a negotiation regarding her stalker problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.75,0:01:03.90,Character Card,,0,0,0,,{\blur2\be5\fad(0,0)}Kobuku Akiho (28)\NClient
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.57,0:01:08.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The body wasn't there when Attorney Kisaki returned her room...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.45,0:01:11.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But was said to appear out of nowhere while she was taking a shower.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.46,0:01:18.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Looks like the culprit moved the bed\Nand hid under it along with the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.63,0:01:27.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Accompanied by Inspector Yokomizo, we began questioning\Nall of the hotel guests with connections to Akiho{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.81,0:01:50.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If we continue lamenting the passing seasons...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.61,0:01:52.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We'll be unable to confront the mysteries of cases!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.66,0:01:54.50,Dialogue,,0,0,5,,Fulfill Ran's wish, Uncle...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.50,0:01:56.25,Dialogue,,0,0,5,,With your famous deduction but without sleeping!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.42,0:01:58.08,Dialogue,,0,0,5,,{\fad(0,0)\xshad1.3\1c&H6AE8FA&\4c&H294A50&\}Perceiving the one and only truth...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.08,0:01:59.88,Dialogue,,0,0,5,,{\fad(0,0)\xshad1.3\1c&H6AE8FA&\4c&H294A50&\}The appearance of a child and the intellect of an adult...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.88,0:02:02.21,Dialogue,,0,0,5,,{\fad(0,50)\xshad1.3\1c&H6AE8FA&\4c&H294A50&\}His name is: Detective {\t(1500,1501,\1c&H4331B1&)}Conan{\1c&H6AE8FA&}!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.30,0:03:34.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My wife!?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.31,0:03:36.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.22,0:03:36.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And, why?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.35,0:03:40.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We're currently investigating that.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.19,0:03:43.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, why did you not pick your wife up?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.63,0:03:48.11,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,I did call and say I'd pick her up, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.14,0:03:50.83,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,She bellowed that she wouldn't let me even if I came over.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.28,0:03:49.16,Signs,,0,0,0,,Kobuku Takehito (30)\NAkiho's Husband
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.57,0:03:53.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And, what was the cause of your argument?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.66,0:03:55.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, it was...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.74,0:03:56.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,About this, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.54,0:04:01.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A bunch of mini cars!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.88,0:04:06.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've loved cars since I was a kid, and lining them up helps me feel calm.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.30,0:04:07.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.17,0:04:09.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How was this the cause of the fight?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.84,0:04:10.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because, see...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.43,0:04:14.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The side mirror was tossed on the floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.64,0:04:17.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A car-loving man wouldn't do something this violent, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.60,0:04:20.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, your wife did this?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.35,0:04:21.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.39,0:04:24.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She told me to quit this childish and disgusting stuff and threw it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.19,0:04:26.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.11,0:04:28.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Which one of these cars is your favorite?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.52,0:04:30.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.78,0:04:33.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The beloved car of the legendary actor, James Dean...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.62,0:04:36.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This Porsche.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.25,0:04:40.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That woman was...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.91,0:04:47.52,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Well, I always figured one of the foolish\Nmen she deceived would eventually kill her.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.05,0:04:46.14,Signs,,0,0,0,,Hino Midori (51)\NOpposing Party in the Negotiations
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.09,0:04:52.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,On that note, it's my understanding that you called the victim.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.01,0:04:53.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.30,0:04:59.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was calling the attorney to see if we could{\rHonorifics - Dialogue} chan{\r}ge\Nthe time of our negotiation tomorrow just a little bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.31,0:05:02.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I was shocked when that woman picked up the phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.48,0:05:06.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why did you aim to{\rHonorifics - Dialogue} chan{\r}ge the time?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.94,0:05:09.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The golf appointment I have with a friend got moved up.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.32,0:05:15.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Going to play golf so soon after your stalker\Nof a son's settlement negotiations?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.16,0:05:16.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This room...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.58,0:05:18.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Has another occupant.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.04,0:05:23.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because these cigarette butts don't have lipstick on them...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.58,0:05:26.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the filter...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.38,0:05:28.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is still damp.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.88,0:05:29.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's true!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.63,0:05:31.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.88,0:05:36.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's enough, Seiji!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.64,0:05:37.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Get out here!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.98,0:05:43.40,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,So that's your stalker so—!?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.48,0:05:43.39,Character Card,,0,0,0,,{\blur2\be5\fad(210,0)}Hino Seiji (26)\NMidori's Son
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.39,0:05:46.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I told you my son was only deceived!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.02,0:05:49.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, you were instructed not to bring your son here, were you not?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.86,0:05:57.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, he happened to be here because he's touring\Nwith his friends on their bikes tomorrow morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.45,0:06:00.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, show us that bike!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.20,0:06:03.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.62,0:06:07.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.25,0:06:11.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A road bike, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.21,0:06:17.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Incidentally, please share with us your whereabouts\Nand actions between 10:00 and 11:00 PM.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.59,0:06:20.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was drinking with Mama.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.60,0:06:22.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you think we're lying, verify it yourself!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.18,0:06:25.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We were at the hotel lounge on the uppermost floor!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.19,0:06:35.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It certainly appears that the mother and son\Nwere drinking together from 9:00 to 12:00.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.41,0:06:39.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And it seems they both left once to go to the restroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.66,0:06:44.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But it was at different times, so the two\Nof them couldn't have moved the bed.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.50,0:06:47.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, it's getting late now.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.83,0:06:49.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's continue the investigation at dawn...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.79,0:06:52.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And, where do you propose I stay?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.21,0:06:55.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why not just stay in Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s room?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.67,0:06:57.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You two are a married couple.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.51,0:06:59.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But living separately, I should note.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.81,0:07:06.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, this was inevitable.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.10,0:07:11.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Something's under the pillow.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.48,0:07:13.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A present?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.32,0:07:16.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Uncle had it prepared after all, didn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.45,0:07:20.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But why didn't he give it to her yesterday, on October 10th?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.36,0:07:23.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,October 10th is my mom's birthday.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.16,0:07:27.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm gonna win first place and give the red ribbon to her as a present!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.42,0:07:31.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't tell me, Uncle...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.08,0:07:33.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can't raise it and then lower it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.55,0:07:38.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Gotta lower then raise the expectation for a surprise...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.76,0:07:40.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Raise and then lower...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.93,0:07:43.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Lower and then raise?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.06,0:07:52.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see, so that's how it was...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.06,0:07:56.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The culprit utilized that to move the bed so quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.24,0:08:00.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Without anyone's help, they did it single-handedly.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.46,0:08:04.58,Dialogue,,0,0,5,,{\b0\fad(460,0)}October 11th
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.08,0:08:04.58,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Hold it, hold it!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.41,0:08:08.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We finally had the{\rHonorifics - Dialogue} chan{\r}ce to stay at a hotel as a family!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.79,0:08:10.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And this is a buffet!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.83,0:08:13.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So why are you sitting at different tables?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.75,0:08:18.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was I who sat down first.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.59,0:08:22.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Doesn't that make the one who purposely sat\Nat another table that mustached old man?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.97,0:08:24.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It can't be helped.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.85,0:08:26.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I have a lot on my mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.47,0:08:33.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Such as how I'm going to prove the innocence\Nof my wife, who has become a murder suspect.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.15,0:08:35.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.57,0:08:37.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ran, don't be fooled.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.36,0:08:40.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's no telling what he's up to.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.65,0:08:41.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mom!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.07,0:08:45.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's checking the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.62,0:08:48.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then checking the present.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.66,0:08:51.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because that moment is approaching...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.83,0:08:54.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's starting to raise the expectation of the receiver, I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.50,0:09:01.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, might as well put Uncle to sleep and solve this case quickly!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.30,0:09:04.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Damn...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.59,0:09:05.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At such a critical moment...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.01,0:09:11.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why can't I find the key to solving this case at all?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.52,0:09:12.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Damn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.44,0:09:19.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, since this special day only comes once\Na year, I'll let Uncle show off this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.82,0:09:25.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It looks like a dish is being brought out!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.45,0:09:27.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How amazing.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.62,0:09:30.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Something so heavy is being moved by a single person.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.00,0:09:32.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's not amazing.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.96,0:09:35.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,With there being tires on the bottom...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.50,0:09:36.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's easy for a single person.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.09,0:09:39.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tires on the bottom?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.67,0:09:42.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, what kind of dish is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.13,0:09:43.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Take a look.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.76,0:09:47.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sausages!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.01,0:09:48.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They look good!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.85,0:09:53.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The ketchup...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.52,0:09:55.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.44,0:09:56.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are you doing!?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.73,0:09:59.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's all right, I'll just bring another one out.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.36,0:10:01.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Geez.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.24,0:10:06.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.57,0:10:10.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The ketchup marks look like dot-dot-dot!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.04,0:10:14.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't it incredible that the marks are evenly spaced?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.54,0:10:15.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Idiot.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.92,0:10:17.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's nothing incredible at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.21,0:10:24.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because the ketchup on the tire will leave a mark on the\Nground as it rolls, the result is the evenly spaced...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.51,0:10:26.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.09,0:10:27.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This mark...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.43,0:10:29.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where have I...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.61,0:10:41.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.77,0:10:43.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's what happened!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.48,0:10:44.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You finally got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.82,0:10:46.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ran!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.90,0:10:48.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Call Yokomizo now!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.41,0:10:52.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Have him gather the suspects in the\Nroom where the crime took place!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.20,0:10:54.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, does that mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.87,0:10:57.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I figured it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.33,0:11:01.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The trick behind that locked room\Nmurder, and the culprit why devised it!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.96,0:11:06.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mouri Kogorou's deduction show is about to begin!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.85,0:11:19.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sorry, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.27,0:11:21.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It took us a while to get here.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.61,0:11:25.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because by the time Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} had contacted us...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.86,0:11:29.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,These three had already checked out of the hotel.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.78,0:11:32.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So why did you call us here?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.37,0:11:34.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I thought there wasn't anything left to talk about.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.66,0:11:38.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I bet they still feel...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.08,0:11:40.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Suspicious toward us.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.37,0:11:42.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's this about?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.21,0:11:44.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't we have an alibi?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.09,0:11:48.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,From 10:00 to 11:00, the supposed time of the crime...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.01,0:11:51.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My son and I were drinking in the hotel lounge!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.43,0:11:54.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But it seems you both left to use the restroom once.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.89,0:11:56.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But separately!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.72,0:11:58.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And each was only for about ten minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.89,0:12:03.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Also, the corpse was in the room where that attorney was staying.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.86,0:12:10.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When the attorney came back at\N11:00, the woman's body wasn't there.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.74,0:12:18.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And if the body was discovered around midnight after she\Nwas taking a shower and let Detective Mouri in the room...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.04,0:12:21.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, isn't this a locked room murder!?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.21,0:12:23.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.71,0:12:27.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since the doors are auto-locked, you can't get in without a keycard.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.34,0:12:32.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If my wife was in the room, she could\Nhave opened the door for me, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.97,0:12:36.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When you returned to the room, my wife wasn't there, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.06,0:12:37.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.06,0:12:37.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.56,0:12:40.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She already was in the room.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.81,0:12:41.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Your wife, I mean.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.44,0:12:46.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Already killed and hidden under the bed.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.53,0:12:50.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Under the bed?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.11,0:12:50.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It can't be...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.86,0:12:56.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then the culprit moved the bed during Eri's shower...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.53,0:12:59.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Revealing the body and fleeing this room immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.50,0:13:01.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Moved the bed?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.50,0:13:03.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But how?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.63,0:13:05.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please wait a moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.38,0:13:07.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is this all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.80,0:13:09.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Without doing your usual thing...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.80,0:13:10.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Usual thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.34,0:13:12.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This thing!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.14,0:13:17.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.97,0:13:18.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The hell was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.02,0:13:20.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.39,0:13:24.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Can you tell us how the bed was moved?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.65,0:13:25.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.40,0:13:28.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Before I returned to the room...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.02,0:13:30.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If the culprit had killed Akiho{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.82,0:13:33.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Concealed the body under the moved bed...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.90,0:13:36.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then hid themselves next to the body...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.53,0:13:39.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I probably couldn't have noticed them when I came in.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.49,0:13:42.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And while I was showering...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.29,0:13:49.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's possible that they moved the bed back in order to\Nreveal the body, and then escaped the room, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.63,0:13:57.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's a herculean task for a single person to slide\Na bed that heavy without leaving drag marks.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.76,0:14:04.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even if Akiho{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} who was sleeping in my room was killed\Nby her husband, Takehiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, when he came to get her...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.81,0:14:06.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He would have been by himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.81,0:14:14.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As for the two of you who knew Akiho{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was in my room,\Nyou could've moved the bed by working together, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.74,0:14:16.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At the time of the crime...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.28,0:14:19.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There was no point in which you were both gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.70,0:14:21.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That makes it impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.99,0:14:26.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Under such circumstances, how did they move the bed and who did it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.62,0:14:27.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mr. Detective?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.38,0:14:30.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By putting tires under the bed.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.50,0:14:32.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tires?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.55,0:14:34.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.01,0:14:36.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Seiji{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} had a road bike.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.88,0:14:40.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He must have utilized the bike's tires!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.93,0:14:42.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Utilized them...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.27,0:14:45.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How did he do it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.02,0:14:46.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It wasn't a bike!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.06,0:14:48.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't it obvious?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.15,0:14:51.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was the person with toys that could easily be placed under the bed.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.27,0:14:54.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By toys, do you mean the mini cars?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.03,0:14:56.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.86,0:15:02.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A single person can lift a bed one corner at\Na time and place the car under each leg.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.83,0:15:08.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,With tires under each of the four bed legs, it would\Nbe easy for a single person to slide the bed.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.08,0:15:12.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The one who lined up the mini cars even in a hotel room...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.38,0:15:14.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Takehiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.92,0:15:15.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was it not you?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.92,0:15:22.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The proof is the small blood tracks near the\Nleg of the bed that are evenly spaced.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.39,0:15:29.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's likely that the mini car tires ran over the bloodstain\Non the carpet while you moved the bed.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.81,0:15:33.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My guess is you've already disposed of those mini cars, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.28,0:15:35.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.69,0:15:42.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If he had just placed the bed on top of the mini\Ncars, it would've slipped off while being moved!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.20,0:15:45.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's true...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.87,0:15:48.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So you didn't figure it out, Uncle?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.71,0:15:55.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't think a man who likes mini cars so much\Nwould do anything like that to damage them.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.01,0:15:59.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because he was so proud of them when he showed me!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.09,0:15:59.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Back then...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.63,0:16:01.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.59,0:16:04.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Which one of these cars is your favorite?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.02,0:16:06.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.27,0:16:09.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The beloved car of the legendary actor, James Dean...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.06,0:16:12.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This Porsche.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.19,0:16:15.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The car that James Dean drove...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.61,0:16:16.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Porsche 911!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.53,0:16:19.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Porsche 911?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.53,0:16:21.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But the car that James Dean drove was...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.41,0:16:25.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Porsche 550 Spyder.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.03,0:16:26.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A convertible.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.54,0:16:27.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.62,0:16:32.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He could've stuck the bed leg into the opening where the seats are!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.00,0:16:36.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That would certainly stabilize it!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.67,0:16:40.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why you couldn't show the 550 Spyder to Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.22,0:16:45.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because the bed leg broke the seats.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.51,0:16:49.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, why didn't Takehiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} leave immediately\Nafter the murder instead of using that trick?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.81,0:16:53.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because if Eri had discovered the body\Nimmediately after returning to the room...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.73,0:17:00.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He'd be the first suspect since she had\Nasked him to come and pick the victim up.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.70,0:17:03.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why, after killing his wife...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.49,0:17:07.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He held the door open using a stopper and returned to his room...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.29,0:17:11.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Before coming back with his mini cars and deploying his trick.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.04,0:17:18.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He figured that if it seemed to be an impossible\Ncrime, it would divert attention away from him.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.13,0:17:20.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.21,0:17:23.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That trick couldn't be used if the\Nattorney hadn't been in the bathroom!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.89,0:17:26.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.30,0:17:28.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was a lucky break for you!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.08,0:17:30.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.18,0:17:33.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Waiting under the bed with a body on such an off{\rHonorifics - Dialogue} chan{\r}ce...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.56,0:17:35.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.02,0:17:37.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No one in their right mind would do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.69,0:17:40.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Encouraged from a few drinks, perhaps?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.90,0:17:42.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't think so.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.19,0:17:43.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Speaking of drinking...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.82,0:17:48.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Whenever Uncle comes home from drinking,\Nhe has something he usually shouts.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.49,0:17:51.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Ran, bring me some water!"
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.79,0:17:54.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's true, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.16,0:17:55.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why are you bringing that up now?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.71,0:18:02.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The reason why one gets thirsty after drinking is that a\Ndehydration reaction occurs as the body breaks down alcohol.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.01,0:18:08.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You already knew I was coming back to the room around 11:00.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.47,0:18:11.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You could've assumed that I was going for a drink with someone.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.97,0:18:12.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.89,0:18:18.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You put only carbonated drinks in my refrigerator...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.06,0:18:20.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And shook up every single can.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.57,0:18:22.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That way, once I had opened it...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.03,0:18:26.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The contents would spray up and force me to take a shower.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.87,0:18:32.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, since we still haven't found the murder weapon...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.66,0:18:38.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why don't we examine the glass ashtray in\NRoom 309 where Takehiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was staying?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.92,0:18:43.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems all of the rooms have those ashtrays.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.38,0:18:47.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If he took the murder weapon with him to make\Nit seem like an extremely impossible crime...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.59,0:18:52.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He would have to switch it with the one in this room.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.77,0:18:57.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A short time later...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.27,0:19:00.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A luminol reaction test on the ashtray in Room 309 proved positive.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.15,0:19:03.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was Akiho{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.78,0:19:06.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Takehiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} also confessed to the crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.65,0:19:09.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The motive was the mini cars.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.82,0:19:15.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He had heard that Akiho{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, a former race queen,\Nliked mini cars, so they hit it off and got married.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.25,0:19:22.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But she laughed and said it was all a lie\Nto lure a wealthy man like Takehiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.55,0:19:26.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What pushed him over the edge...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.84,0:19:28.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Were her final words.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.18,0:19:30.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say, did you figure out?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.97,0:19:33.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The meaning of that birthday present I gave you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.43,0:19:37.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The 550 Spyder?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.39,0:19:41.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was the beloved car of a famous movie star, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.52,0:19:43.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A car that can't be bought unless you're rich.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.57,0:19:49.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In other words, it means I only married you because of your money.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.24,0:19:51.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I can't wait to inherit it after your death!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.29,0:20:00.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was quite a present, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.00,0:20:04.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I wouldn't want to get something like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.34,0:20:07.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My, I think it beats getting nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.51,0:20:11.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, I'm heading home.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.51,0:20:14.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You aren't going back to the hotel?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.81,0:20:16.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's already 11:00!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.47,0:20:17.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.89,0:20:19.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've already called a taxi.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.48,0:20:20.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,See you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.48,0:20:21.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.44,0:20:26.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Although there's only an hour left, it's still your birthday.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.94,0:20:28.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why don't we celebrate, just the two of us?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.44,0:20:31.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We'll send Ran and the brat off to another room...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.49,0:20:36.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And return to the time when we were lovers.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.04,0:20:40.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is a little something from me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.08,0:20:46.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, since you're an adult, I guess you won't be\Nthrilled to get something trivial like a birthday present.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.71,0:20:47.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,May I ask...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.96,0:20:49.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Whose birthday is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.63,0:20:51.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why, yours of course!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.59,0:20:52.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Same as Health & Sports Day!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.35,0:21:00.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Speaking of Health & Sports Day, it\Nused to be on October 10th, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.89,0:21:02.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.02,0:21:05.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But now it falls on the second Monday in October.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.98,0:21:13.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't tell me Dad only remembers Mom's\Nbirthday through Health & Sports Day?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.11,0:21:18.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's because you always said it at the\Nsports event when we were kids!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.54,0:21:21.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Today's my birthday, so I can't lose!"
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.21,0:21:27.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,October 10th is usually a bright and sunny day, so\Nschools used to hold their sports event on that day.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.92,0:21:30.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What the...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.59,0:21:33.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I purposely lowered and then raised it!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.63,0:21:35.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So it was all meaningless?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.47,0:21:37.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Lowered and then raised it?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.51,0:21:39.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why you were so cold to Mom!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.14,0:21:42.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You didn't need to lower her expectations...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.35,0:21:44.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In any case...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.98,0:21:48.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll gladly accept these spoils of war.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.23,0:21:51.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You clumsy detective...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.29,0:23:24.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the next day...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.00,0:23:25.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.20,0:23:27.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What in the world is this!?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.17,0:23:29.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The contents of the present!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.21,0:23:32.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I thought it was a necklace...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.00,0:23:33.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But they're prayer beads!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.51,0:23:37.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is he telling me to die?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.22,0:23:37.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That man!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.13,0:23:43.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The manager at Poirot asked Dad to buy those prayer beads...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.10,0:23:45.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It looks like he brought the wrong thing along by mistake...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.65,0:23:53.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There it is!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.32,0:23:57.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Uncle, that's too big of a mistake...
